            <ab>Dec. 30, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>J. A. Rowland, Esq.</ab>
            <ab>Washington, D. C.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I am directed by the Attorney General to inform you that your services will not be required in this Department after the end of the present month.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
            <ab>A. J. Falls,</ab>
            <ab>Chief Clerk.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">cessation of services</note>
